<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 flex flex-col">
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-4">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div>
          <%= link_to root_path, class: "hover:opacity-70" do %>
            <h1 class="text-4xl">ðŸ““</h1>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <% if authenticated? %>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700"><%= Current.session.user.email_address %></span>
            <%= button_to "Sign out", session_path, method: :delete, class: "text-sm text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 underline" %>
          <% else %>
            <%= link_to "Sign in", new_session_path, class: "text-sm text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-900 underline" %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-8">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About Jotter</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Jotter is a personal project by <%= link_to "Stephen McCullough (swmcc)", "https://swmcc.github.io", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4 mt-8">Bookmarks</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          I built this as a way to keep interesting bookmarks on my own server, where I own the data and don't have to rely on third-party apps. Remember <%= link_to "Delicious", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delicious_(website)", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %>? It was brilliant until Yahoo bought it and it eventually disappeared, taking everyone's carefully curated bookmarks with it. Never again.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
          With Jotter, my bookmarks live on my own infrastructure. They're mine, they're private (unless I choose to share them), and they'll be here as long as I want them to be.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4 mt-8">Images</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Same story with images. <%= link_to "Twitpic", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitpic", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %> shut down in 2014 and took millions of photos with it. Photobucket started charging people to access their own images. I'm tired of trusting other people's servers with my stuff.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
          Now my photos are here, on my own infrastructure. They'll be around as long as I am.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Colophon</h3>

          <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
            <p>
              <strong>Built with:</strong> Ruby on Rails 8, PostgreSQL, Tailwind CSS v4, and Hotwire
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Deployed on:</strong> My own server (because that's the whole point)
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Features:</strong> Bookmark management with browser bookmarklet, image galleries and albums with drag-and-drop uploads, tagging, public/private visibility, short URLs with Slack/Discord preview support, and background image processing
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Source code:</strong> <%= link_to "ðŸ™ Available on GitHub", "https://github.com/swmcc/jotter", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
        <%= link_to "â† Back to Home", root_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%= render "shared/footer" %>
</div>
